Below are the software keyboard templates. The Format for these is as follows:
cCxX:

c = Lowercase character
C = Uppercase version of the character
x = Lowercase variant of character (ie '' is a variant of 'e')
X = Uppercase version of the lowercase variant
: = terminator for this character

Note: You can repeat the xX pair with as many variants as you want (ie for the letter 'e' formatting would be:
eE:
Select a challenge to compete in. Only the fastest times are awarded a high score!
Configure the controls to suit your style of play.
Create your own teams, weapons and game styles to suit your tastes.
Game styles contain game and weapon settings.
Advanced users can create game styles to change the game and weapon settings.
Insert a team or change team settings.
Use the money youve earned to buy a multitude of cool items and wormy additions!
Level Code: %u Right Click to randomise.
Select a landscape to battle on.
Select the mission you want to play, then go for it!
Personalise everything about your team! Remember kids, don't leave your worm naked in the cold!
Sit back, relax and take pride in your achievements.
Complete the tutorials in order to improve your worming skills.
Create and balance your team weapon. Keep the pressure gauge out of the red to maintain weapon stability.
Wormpot modifies the game rules to create new ways to play.
Spin those reels! Press the "green" button for information or "red" to reset.

At last, I have managed to find some of the loot that nasty Ali Baboon stole from the lovely Queen. Get up here and help me get it back down to the ground.No you dont need your weapons, just leave them down there.

Well it seems Ali Baboon has had enough of us picking on his gang. He has informed me that if we can manage to get through his Thief Training Course, and get to him we can have all the Queens jewels back. Well what are you waiting for? You dont expect me to put my life in danger do you?

After a long chase, weve cornered a couple of Ali Baboons thieves. They think they can escape NOT A CHANCE! Get up that walkway and dispose of all the thieving worms before they can steal from anyone else. Well what you waiting for? Hop to it!

Some of Ali Baboons gang are using stolen galleons to torment the small village of Wormamhabad. They are forcing the people to give up their worldly possessions in exchange for their lives. I dont like bullies!! Take out their guns and send them to a watery grave!

I have noticed some of Ali Baboons cohorts hanging around this market place and I think they are planning on using the cover of darkness to steal all of the market traders goods. We must help the local law enforcement agents capture these rascals. Get those criminals into the jail yard and the police will do the rest!
Do you want this team to be player controlled?
Use /*KEY.PS2.DPAD*/ to position the screen,/*NL*//*KEY.PS2.CROSS*/ to accept and/*NL*//*KEY.PS2.TRIANGLE*/ to cancel.
Use your Poison Arrow to poison all the worms in the fastest time possible. You will need a cool eye and a steady hand to succeed.
Use any of your skills to navigate around the landscape and collect all the crates in the fastest time possible.
Flap your way around the level collecting the crates. Grab them all in the fastest time to claim glory.
Fly around the level collecting the crates in a fast paced test of your Jet Pack skills.
Hot step your way to the top of the path. Fastest time wins.
Get the Old Woman across the building site to the bus stop in the fastest time possible. You will have to use all of her abilities to succeed.
Swoop down and collect all the targets before finally reaching the ground. Use the parachute to control your speed of descent.
Use your shotgun to hit the moving targets as they fall in front of you. Get them all and get them quick.
Use your Sniper Rifle to pick off the targets around the town. Speed is of the essence and accuracy a must.
Use your faithful Super Sheep to navigate around the level collecting the crates as you go.
Each team begins in control of their own fort for tactical play. Deathmatch rules apply.

This is the enemys main building supply location. From here they can supply building materials to all their military establishments. Lets tackle the root of the problem shall we? Blow up their diggers and really put their Logistics Department out of action. Then we can sit back and examine the effects.

Oh cripes! Weve been spotted! And I was told the construction of this weapons factory was on hold! It looks like the planning inspectors are here to check it out. Not to worry though, we can get you out of there Just find and get to the escape crate without dying and we can airlift you out of there.

We have taken out all the enemy supply lines and have stopped their military progress. They do still have their new Main Weapons Research Laboratory under construction though. If we can take out this establishment, we will really have the enemy where we want them. So, take out that Weapons Lab!

Okay class, assignment number one. The enemy are about to open their newly constructed worm eatery, a place they intend to use to feed their armies. Lets put a stop to their plan and see how the enemy march on an empty stomach shall we?

Supply lines are a key factor to providing equipment to frontline forces. The enemy doesnt seem to think they are that important though. Lets see the cause and effect of disabling one of their main supply lines. Take away the workmens tools while they are out to lunch, be quick though, theyll be back soon!
Are you sure you want to buy this?
Are you sure you want to delete this?
You must eliminate all enemies on the landscape. But wait! There's a twist! Only the quickest times will make the high score table.
Remove all traces of enemy worms. The quickest times will be forever remembered on the high score table.
It's a gritty deathmatch! Destroy all enemy worms as quickly as you can. The quickest times will find fame on the high score table.
This deathmatch challenge requires all enemy worms to be destroyed. Do it quickly and your time may find a place on the high score table.
It's a fight to the death!  Take out the enemy worms in the quickest time possible to achieve a place on the high score table.
Enemy worms have gathered on a nearby island. Destroy them as quick as possible to obtain a position on the high score table.
Enemy worms detected. Seek and destroy all hostiles. Kill as quickly as you can to gain a place on the high score table.
This deathmatch challenge requires all enemies to be eliminated. The quickest times will be rewarded with a place on the high score table.
A rival platoon have been found nearby. Eradicate them as quickly as you can to gain a place on the high score table.
We have a problem. Kill all enemy worms. Do it as quickly as possible to get a place on the high score table.
The classic multi player mode where the last surviving team is declared the winner.
A nice simple mission to get you started. Collect the crates and kill the bad guys.
Sorry, this feature is only available in the full game.
A race to destroy the enemy's base. The coloured bars on screen show the remaining land for each player.
If this is your first play we recommend you create your own team.

Look at what lies between you and me: a river of prehistoric proportions! You will never be able to cross it! Those stepping stones are made for dinosaurs, not worms! And besides, the locals control this crossing, and you dont really want to get involved with them!

Ha ha, now youre stuck!! You are never going to be able to get down that mountain and its the only way through to where I am! Its just too steep! Add to that the savage natives and maniacal beasts that roam around here and you will never make it down alive!!!

Just a minor setback I will have this fixed in no time. Meanwhile you have a herd of hungry dinosaurs to deal with, and oh dear! All their food has been spilled from their cooking pot. There is no way you can gather it all up and throw it back in the pot before the ice caps melt and send you to a watery grave!

Oh dear! It seems you are a worm down. It looks like one of you has wandered off a little too far from the pack. Are you willing to save your own classmate? Even when there are caveworms, dinosaurs and an extremely volatile volcano in your way? Face it, its over for you now. Get used to the Prehistoric life!

Bah!!! I dont know how you managed to get across to me alive but it doesnt matter: you still wont get to me. My crash seems to have attracted a few of the locals and they now stand in between you and me. There is no way you will manage to fend them off before I get this fixed and leave you here stranded forever!!!

These wizards are way too cheeky for my liking. The Battle Wizard has put up a piece of our time machine as a prize in a jousting competition! You will have to go in there and beat all of the knights who are taking part to claim that prize. Without it we are going nowhere

Well done class! Weve finally retrieved all of the time machine parts all we have to do now is put it back together. Good job weve found this deserted castle: it will provide good shelter from the rain and perhaps even this army who are hot on our trail! Keep me safe while I put this thing back together and then well make good our escape.

This is the stronghold of the Rogue Wizard, a dastardly fellow at best. He has another of the time machines components stashed deep in the dungeons of his castle and is not going to come out without a fight. Despatch his bandit guards and he will soon appear, along with the part. Then we can show him what dastardly tactics are all about.

Those medieval oafs have ransacked the time machine and made off with some vital parts! We will have to get them back if we want to get out of here.  Apparently the wizard that lives in this castle has one but he has it very heavily guarded. Lets storm our way in there and retrieve it.

Well, I have found the location of the time machines dashboard enhancement problem is, its being used by The Windy Wizard to control the wind! We will have to take out his power supply before we can attack him but watch out, I hear the Wizards apprentices are in the area and theyre crack-shots!
Please wait, searching for a game
Please wait, searching for a game
Destroy the enemy's statues while trying to defend your own. The team with the remaining statue wins the game.
Each team uses one worm at a time to defeat the enemy. Death of a worm will spawn another until all your team is out.

Oh dear, attendances are down this year if I dont have any students to pass on my great knowledge to, what will I do? Ill have to close the University and I hope it doesnt come to that. I do hope some students stop by soon

Team, I need your help with something. Lets take a peek at one of the Universitys more impressive properties, our teams sports stadium! Only, weve got a little problem... a few things need cleaning up. Come along, you might learn a thing or two!

Ive been impressed by how well youve been doing so far, so Ive decided to let you in on a little secret. Blindfolds on, no peeking! Were travelling across the waters, heading towards a Top Secret Location!
The Blimp View camera will be disabled.
Weapons can only be obtained through crate drops.
A crate shower will arrive at the start of every turn.
Changes the normally harmless prod function into a health sapping death touch.
Whenever a worm dies its complete inventory is left for anyone to collect.
Everything does twice the amount of damage.
No wormpot mode selected on this reel.
All worms are poisoned, cure your worms or kill the enemy.
There is no land, only girders, and thats the only way to get around.
One of your worms is the mighty Goliath (lots of energy) and the rest are Davids (not much energy).
Worms can only jump to get around the landscape.
Gravity has less of an effect on worms making them jump higher.
More than one girder can be placed during one turn.
Fall damage will hurt worms a lot.
The landscape is indestructible and any mine that explodes will respawn again and again.
This will stop the worms ability to drop weapons whilst using movement utilities.
Worms lose their ability to jump and can only walk around the landscape.
All worms start with 1 health so one shot does indeed mean one kill.
Worms will be able to walk a lot faster than normal.
A random weapon in the inventory will do super damage.
Worms will slide around the landscape more easily.
Each worm on the team will have a special weapon set.
Worms will stick to the landscape more and be harder to move around.
All animal weapons do increased damage and will throw worms further than usual.
All cluster weapons do increased damage and will throw worms further than usual.
All explosive weapons do increased damage and will throw worms further than usual.
All firearm weapons do increased damage and will throw worms further than usual.
All melee weapons do increased damage and will throw worms further than usual.
One of your worms is a vampire. Half the damage he inflicts on another worm is gifted back to him.
One worm on each team is vital, if he dies the team dies.
Wind affects all weapons in the game, even the grenade.
Gun wobble is affected by the wind speed.
Wind affects worms when jumping or knocked into the air.
Worms can only be killed by knocking them into the water, no health is removed via a shot.
This weapon is way too unstable! You should reduce the power or it will take your face off!

The river bed here is apparently chocked full of golden nuggets perfect fuel for the time machine, however, the locals dont seem to want us to take it away. They are about to blow open the J.C. Van Dam and flood the whole area. Get to the high ground and then teach those varmints a lesson!

Rumour has it that Boggy the Kid hides some of his gold in the graves of the worms he has killed. Oooh creepy! Have a look round this graveyard and see what you can find. Try not to disturb any of the graves though; the guys buried here will not take kindly to being disturbed!

We almost have enough gold, but still need a little more. Its time to pay this Boggy the Kid character a visit. We will need to sneak into his base and get someone to open the gate for us. Then we can surprise his gang and take them out before they have a chance to react. Once his gang is defeated,  we can be away with his gold and finally get home.

Ok class, this is it. Weve found Gold Mountain and I believe that theres enough gold here to send us halfway home! Theres just one small thing; some of Boggy the Kids gang are hanging out by the entrance. They are not going to let us just walk off with their gold, so we will just have to persuade them.

Im sorry to say class, that I may have made a mistake. I was drinking in a bar last night when I overheard a ruffian called Tin Can Wally bragging about his gold stash. I tried asking him to give it to me, but he got a little angry and now he wants a duel at dawn! Well being the pacifist that I am, one of you will have to fight in my place! Good luck!
